      "sectionId": 6,
      "subheading": "Benefits of Docker for Teachers",
      "content": [
        {
          "link": "",
          "text": "Docker is a free tool thus eliminating the need for students to install anything locally and saving valuable time."
        },
        {
          "link": "",
          "text": "Docker has the most up to date presentations, hands-on labs, workshops etc. on every topic and for every skill level."
        },
        {
          "link": "",
          "text": "Docker provides a dedicated support to help you through the process. It also has an online Docker Teachers community where you can collaborate and learn from other educators."
        },
        {
          "link": "https://blog.docker.com/2017/09/docker-higher-education-tools-resources-teachers/",
          "text": "For more information..."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "sectionId": 7,
      "subheading": "Benefits of Docker for Students",
      "content": [
        {
          "link": "",
          "text": "Docker is a very important skills to learn if you've a career in tech."
        },
        {
          "link": "",
          "text": "Students can just start coding instead of spending time setting up the environment. Since every member in group will have the same environment so Docker eliminates any ‘works on my machine’ issues."
        },
        {
          "link": "",
          "text": "Docker allows you to easily build applications with a modern microservices architecture also greatly enhancing the security of your applications."
        },
        {
          "link": "https://blog.docker.com/2017/05/announcing-docker-student-developer-kit-campus-ambassador-program/",
          "text": "For more information..."
        }
      ]
    },
